=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_TGaussRand_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark clean sound, with sine_like oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring moderate attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: moderate
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: clean
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.0343
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9752
  pitch_clarity: 61.1187
  inharmonicity: 0.3807
  type: sine_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.4134
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: TGaussRand Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/TGaussRand.html
// Tags: TGaussRand, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
{
    var trig;
    trig = Dust.kr(10);
    Pan2.ar(SinOsc.ar(
            TGaussRand.kr(300, 3000, trig)
        ),
        TGaussRand.kr(-1, 1, trig),
        0.1
    )
}.play;
)
